1
00:00:56,599 --> 00:00:58,142
- [thudding]
- [Seol-ah gasps]

2
00:00:58,225 --> 00:01:00,102
[groans] <i>Let go of me!</i> [screams]

3
00:01:06,525 --> 00:01:07,568
[gasps]

4
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:15,743
[sobbing]

5
00:01:33,177 --> 00:01:35,179
[tense orchestral music plays]

6
00:01:49,652 --> 00:01:50,653
Don't you move.

7
00:01:56,158 --> 00:01:58,160
[dramatic choral music plays]

8
00:02:09,964 --> 00:02:11,549
[panting]

9
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:44,123
Hands up, don't move!

10
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:05,686
Freeze!

11
00:03:07,605 --> 00:03:10,441
- No.
- Take one more step, and I'll shoot.

12
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:24,663
[panting]

13
00:03:25,998 --> 00:03:27,750
[grunting]

14
00:03:30,794 --> 00:03:31,795
Are you okay?

15
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:37,301
Seol-ah.

16
00:03:37,384 --> 00:03:39,803
What the hell happened, huh?

17
00:03:45,309 --> 00:03:46,310
Seol-ah, tell me.

18
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:19,760
Arrest that woman.

19
00:04:20,928 --> 00:04:22,680
Hold on. No!

20
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:23,889
Let go!

21
00:04:24,556 --> 00:04:26,433
God damn it! Hey!

22
00:04:27,434 --> 00:04:28,644
Seol-ah. Let go!

23
00:04:29,144 --> 00:04:30,521
This is a murder case!

24
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:32,064
Get it together, damn it.

25
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:37,695
- [poignant song playing]
- Come on.

26
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:41,031
Han Seol-ah. You're under arrest
for the murder of Paek Jun-beom.

27
00:04:41,115 --> 00:04:43,909
You have the right to remain silent,
and the right to an attorney.

28
00:04:43,993 --> 00:04:46,078
Anything you say or do
can and will be used

29
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:47,246
against you in a court of law.

30
00:04:47,746 --> 00:04:49,915
Do you understand the rights
I've just read to you?

31
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:52,876
Take her.

32
00:05:26,785 --> 00:05:29,079
{\an8}EPISODE 9

33
00:05:29,163 --> 00:05:30,164
{\an8}[shutter clicking]

34
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:39,256
{\an8}DIED AUGUST 27, 2025
DATED, THEN PROPOSED

35
00:05:48,599 --> 00:05:49,600
{\an8}[grunts]

36
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:11,455
GANGHA POLICE STATION

37
00:06:16,627 --> 00:06:17,628
[Gong] <i>Freeze!</i>

38
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:19,546
<i>Take one more step, and I'll shoot.</i>

39
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:30,224
I've submitted
the firearms discharge report.

40
00:06:30,808 --> 00:06:33,811
You followed the manual.
Cha Woo-seok was the one who jumped in.

41
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:38,398
Woo-seok's injuries aren't serious.

42
00:06:39,525 --> 00:06:41,360
Luckily, the bullet only grazed him.

43
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,488
You didn't do anything wrong.

44
00:06:45,614 --> 00:06:46,907
Forget about it, okay?

45
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:49,660
Sure.

46
00:06:59,086 --> 00:07:00,087
[line dialing]

47
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:27,865
The weapon was inside.

48
00:07:28,407 --> 00:07:30,075
[Seol-ah] Get off me! Let go of me!

49
00:07:31,702 --> 00:07:32,870
Don't do this.

50
00:07:32,953 --> 00:07:34,454
Stay away.

51
00:07:34,538 --> 00:07:36,540
I already died once because of you.

52
00:07:38,542 --> 00:07:40,294
Why not make it twice now?

53
00:07:58,729 --> 00:07:59,730
[Gong] Ms. Han Seol-ah.

54
00:08:00,898 --> 00:08:02,065
Ms. Han Seol-ah.

55
00:08:07,696 --> 00:08:09,781
Are you going to keep refusing to talk?

56
00:08:13,327 --> 00:08:14,620
<i>Can you not hear me?</i>

57
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:18,332
[Seong-il] You think you can keep this up?

58
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,836
Ms. Han Seol-ah. You know
you were caught in the act, right?

59
00:08:24,463 --> 00:08:26,131
You can't just walk out of here.

60
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:37,517
[scoffs] She's not right in the head.

61
00:08:39,061 --> 00:08:41,897
[Seong-il] What? Planning to plead
diminished capacity?

62
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:45,108
If this is just an act until then,
then that's clever.

63
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:47,402
Right.

64
00:08:47,903 --> 00:08:49,571
If you wanna get away with murder,

65
00:08:50,572 --> 00:08:52,115
you better act really well.

66
00:09:03,043 --> 00:09:05,545
[intriguing music plays]

67
00:09:11,134 --> 00:09:12,302
[shutter clicking]

68
00:09:16,848 --> 00:09:18,558
[Woo-seok] <i>Honeycomb-textured gloves.</i>

69
00:09:24,398 --> 00:09:26,441
<i>Someone intentionally flipped the breaker.</i>

70
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:56,972
If someone else was involved…

71
00:10:02,644 --> 00:10:03,895
<i>they went that way.</i>

72
00:10:07,691 --> 00:10:09,693
[intense music plays]

73
00:11:05,499 --> 00:11:07,417
- [door opens]
- I mean, this makes no sense.

74
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:09,628
- [door closes]
- Killing a VIP client?

75
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:11,254
We can't keep shielding Ms. Han.

76
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:12,881
It's our chance to fire her.

77
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:15,175
Is that important now?

78
00:11:15,258 --> 00:11:17,094
[stammers] If not, what?

79
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:20,555
The owner of the Stiller painting
is dead now!

80
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:22,182
That was supposed to be the highest piece

81
00:11:22,265 --> 00:11:24,559
in our auction's history,
and now it's blown.

82
00:11:24,643 --> 00:11:25,644
So what now?

83
00:11:25,727 --> 00:11:27,813
What are we going to do?

84
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:29,022
[stammers] True.

85
00:11:29,106 --> 00:11:30,357
You're right. Yeah.

86
00:11:32,234 --> 00:11:34,069
Have Attorney Kim come in.

87
00:11:34,152 --> 00:11:36,446
We'll just take care of Ms. Han first.

88
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:37,697
Got it?

89
00:11:37,781 --> 00:11:38,824
Sure.

90
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:43,036
[sighs]

91
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:48,792
[Eun-gyeom] <i>She's refusing</i>
<i>all visitors and meals.</i>

92
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:53,797
I can't believe they only let us
drop her clothes off.

93
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:55,340
This is nuts.

94
00:11:55,424 --> 00:11:57,300
What is going on with Seol-ah?

95
00:11:57,384 --> 00:12:00,178
[sighs] Why is she acting like this now?

96
00:12:00,262 --> 00:12:02,681
Is she really guilty or something?

97
00:12:11,189 --> 00:12:12,190
[door closes]

98
00:12:16,945 --> 00:12:18,780
The person who died
at the villa last night,

99
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:20,782
it wasn't Paek Jun-beom.

100
00:12:22,451 --> 00:12:25,662
What kind of bullshit is this?
I saw it with my own two eyes.

101
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:29,666
The real Paek Jun-beom died
seven years ago in Syria.

102
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:31,001
- What's that?
- [groans]

103
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,711
Then who's the man that was killed?

104
00:12:33,295 --> 00:12:34,379
Lee Su-ho.

105
00:12:34,463 --> 00:12:35,547
Lee Su-ho?

106
00:12:36,923 --> 00:12:39,593
- Han Seol-ah's ex who died in Syria?
- [Woo-seok] Right.

107
00:12:39,676 --> 00:12:42,095
Paek Jun-beom was also in Syria
at the time.

108
00:12:42,179 --> 00:12:44,264
The one who died there was not Lee Su-ho.

109
00:12:45,307 --> 00:12:46,308
It was Paek Jun-beom.

110
00:12:47,142 --> 00:12:48,894
What the hell are you talking about?

111
00:12:49,436 --> 00:12:52,063
Lee Su-ho had plastic surgery
to look like his dead friend

112
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:55,066
and has been living as Paek Jun-beom
all this time!

113
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:58,445
This isn't a movie. Is that even possible?

114
00:13:00,447 --> 00:13:02,491
H-How did you find that out?

115
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:05,410
His iris.

116
00:13:08,038 --> 00:13:11,583
When Lee Su-ho returned
to the company with Paek Jun-beom's face,

117
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:14,127
the security system didn't recognize him.

118
00:13:14,211 --> 00:13:17,380
The staff assumed it was a malfunction
and replaced the system.

119
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:20,217
Truth is his iris didn't match.

120
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,801
You can change your face,

121
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:24,679
but you can't change your iris.

122
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:30,268
Their DNA records were still in
OnWorld's database, and I verified them.

123
00:13:30,352 --> 00:13:31,770
TEST RESULTS

124
00:13:33,522 --> 00:13:35,357
SAMPLE 1: LEE SU-HO
SAMPLE 2: PAEK JUN-BEOM

125
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:38,401
{\an8}SAMPLE 1 AND SAMPLE 2
ARE FROM THE SAME INDIVIDUAL

126
00:13:42,614 --> 00:13:43,615
LEE SU-HO'S DNA PROFILE

127
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:46,076
PAEK JUN-BEOM'S DNA PROFILE

128
00:13:49,704 --> 00:13:51,915
Even if the victim is Lee Su-ho,
not Paek Jun-beom,

129
00:13:51,998 --> 00:13:53,833
it doesn't change the fact
that Han Seol-ah

130
00:13:53,917 --> 00:13:55,710
was caught red handed at the murder scene.

131
00:13:55,794 --> 00:13:58,797
But evidence of a third party
was discovered at the scene.

132
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,590
Hasn't it been reported yet?

133
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:04,344
[Woo-seok sighs]

134
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:09,099
I'll hand over everything
that I've gathered so far.

135
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:11,560
Just do me this favor.

136
00:14:12,561 --> 00:14:13,562
Han Seol-ah.

137
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,023
Let me see her just one time.

138
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:21,319
Snap out of it, you idiot.
Do you even hear yourself?

139
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:24,114
She's got the right to remain silent.
She's using it.

140
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:25,615
She threw herself
in front of a warning shot.

141
00:14:25,699 --> 00:14:27,284
She's given up on everything!

142
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:28,910
What do you expect her to say?

143
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:32,581
Do you think it'll make a difference
if she met with you?

144
00:14:32,664 --> 00:14:33,999
I'll give it a try.

145
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,502
It won't hurt the investigation.
I'll do whatever you say.

146
00:14:37,586 --> 00:14:40,088
[dramatic music plays]

147
00:15:05,363 --> 00:15:07,949
He was stabbed in the heart before
he had the chance to defend himself.

148
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:10,493
The blade went in horizontally…

149
00:15:12,871 --> 00:15:14,497
and struck the breastbone.

150
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:17,876
The force was so great that it bent
the tip of the weapon.

151
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:19,711
And the suspect?

152
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:21,921
Given the angle and force,

153
00:15:22,005 --> 00:15:25,133
it's likely the suspect is a man
with a similar build.

154
00:15:25,216 --> 00:15:27,761
But Han Seol-ah's fingerprints
were found on the weapon.

155
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:31,973
[sighs] It's not impossible
if we assume the victim was on the ground

156
00:15:32,057 --> 00:15:33,683
when the stabbing occurred, but--

157
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:37,395
Lee Su-ho, the guy Han Seol-ah dumped,
shows up as Paek Jun-beom?

158
00:15:38,021 --> 00:15:41,483
Those men and Kim Yun-ji.
It's obvious it was all him.

159
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:43,443
Those photos he took while stalking her

160
00:15:43,526 --> 00:15:45,153
show how insanely obsessed he was.

161
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:48,239
But this time he's the victim.

162
00:15:48,323 --> 00:15:52,744
Han Seol-ah found out it was Lee Su-ho,
and probably got into an argument.

163
00:15:53,578 --> 00:15:56,122
It escalated and turned into a murder.

164
00:15:59,376 --> 00:16:01,336
People have psychological barriers,

165
00:16:01,419 --> 00:16:03,296
especially when committing a crime.

166
00:16:04,339 --> 00:16:08,009
This was far too cold, too flawless
and too ruthless

167
00:16:08,927 --> 00:16:10,470
to be a first murder.

168
00:16:14,015 --> 00:16:15,183
Let's go.

169
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:18,395
Let's go see if Han Seol-ah
decides to finally talk.

170
00:17:03,815 --> 00:17:04,816
[door closes]

171
00:17:06,484 --> 00:17:07,902
[Seong-il] How's it going?

172
00:17:08,486 --> 00:17:10,864
She still hasn't said a single word.

173
00:17:15,994 --> 00:17:17,746
You're not hurt, are you?

174
00:17:25,003 --> 00:17:26,379
Did you get some sleep?

175
00:17:29,591 --> 00:17:30,884
Have you eaten?

176
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:47,275
[exhales shakily]

177
00:17:51,613 --> 00:17:52,864
How is your arm?

178
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:58,077
It's nothing.

179
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:00,371
It was just a graze.

180
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:02,957
You could've died.

181
00:18:08,129 --> 00:18:09,380
But I didn't, right?

182
00:18:10,006 --> 00:18:12,926
You should've gone to the hospital.
Why are you here?

183
00:18:19,766 --> 00:18:20,767
Paek Jun-beom…

184
00:18:25,063 --> 00:18:26,231
What happened?

185
00:18:29,526 --> 00:18:30,652
Seol-ah.

186
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:38,117
When Paek Jun-beom collapsed
at the auction house,

187
00:18:38,201 --> 00:18:40,161
you realized he was Lee Su-ho.

188
00:18:41,162 --> 00:18:43,122
Then while I was running the DNA test,

189
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,792
he dragged you to the villa.

190
00:18:48,002 --> 00:18:49,838
You have to tell me what happened.

191
00:18:50,672 --> 00:18:52,674
Someone else was at the villa, right?

192
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:54,884
The person who killed him,

193
00:18:56,177 --> 00:18:57,554
did you see him?

194
00:19:15,446 --> 00:19:16,906
Is it your turn next?

195
00:19:22,787 --> 00:19:25,415
I told you I killed my parents,
and you still believed me.

196
00:19:26,374 --> 00:19:28,042
The other men were no different.

197
00:19:28,877 --> 00:19:31,337
If you become Han Seol-ah's man,
you'll be next.

198
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:34,757
Because you'll take out
an insurance policy.

199
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:37,927
Every one of those fools did just that.

200
00:19:39,387 --> 00:19:40,805
And I killed them.

201
00:19:42,932 --> 00:19:43,933
You're lying.

202
00:19:52,358 --> 00:19:54,319
[poignant song playing]

203
00:20:05,246 --> 00:20:06,414
It was so easy.

204
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,586
Everyone said they just pitied me

205
00:20:11,669 --> 00:20:14,047
that they'd do anything for me,

206
00:20:15,256 --> 00:20:17,717
so I told them to do what my parents did…

207
00:20:21,387 --> 00:20:23,306
to get insurance and die.

208
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:29,520
So just…

209
00:20:34,108 --> 00:20:35,693
get away from me now.

210
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:08,601
Are you afraid that I'll get hurt?

211
00:21:10,103 --> 00:21:12,438
You were left to survive alone
against your will,

212
00:21:13,231 --> 00:21:14,607
but you didn't break.

213
00:21:16,234 --> 00:21:17,735
You stayed strong

214
00:21:19,153 --> 00:21:20,655
and you made it this far.

215
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:24,951
You are not the villain here.

216
00:21:26,911 --> 00:21:28,121
You're a survivor.

217
00:21:29,414 --> 00:21:30,957
Han Seol-ah didn't do this,

218
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:33,042
so don't give up now. Tell the truth.

219
00:21:33,126 --> 00:21:34,502
You have to fight and survive.

220
00:21:36,004 --> 00:21:38,214
You can fix everything. I'll help you.

221
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:42,093
You're not alone.

222
00:21:47,265 --> 00:21:48,266
Don't worry.

223
00:21:52,061 --> 00:21:54,063
I'll survive this time too.

224
00:21:58,484 --> 00:22:00,486
[song continues]

225
00:22:04,198 --> 00:22:05,783
Get this man out of here.

226
00:22:06,367 --> 00:22:08,244
He has nothing to do with this case.

227
00:22:33,644 --> 00:22:34,812
[Woo-seok sighs]

228
00:22:40,068 --> 00:22:41,486
I guess we're even now.

229
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:45,740
Don't worry about it.

230
00:22:45,823 --> 00:22:47,283
I'm fine.

231
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:49,285
Sure. Take care of it.

232
00:22:50,286 --> 00:22:52,872
Thank you for letting me see her.

233
00:22:53,456 --> 00:22:55,249
It's not like
we didn't have our own agenda.

234
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:58,336
We wanted to see if she'd talk to you,
that's all.

235
00:23:00,463 --> 00:23:02,298
She doesn't wanna drag me into this.

236
00:23:02,924 --> 00:23:04,634
You saw her lying to push me away.

237
00:23:04,717 --> 00:23:07,595
Did it ever cross your mind
that it might not be a lie?

238
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:10,807
What she said in there could be the truth.

239
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:13,059
She showed me all her wounds.

240
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:15,978
She said she killed them, but her
whole body was saying it wasn't her.

241
00:23:16,062 --> 00:23:17,814
What if she was doing it for sympathy?

242
00:23:17,897 --> 00:23:19,816
Who does that during an interrogation?

243
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:22,318
I'm legal counsel for Royal Auction.

244
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:25,655
Where's Ms. Han Seol-ah?

245
00:23:27,782 --> 00:23:29,534
ROYAL AUCTION
CHIEF AUCTIONEER HAN SEOL-AH

246
00:23:32,662 --> 00:23:34,705
[Na-hee] So, what's going to happen
to Ms. Han?

247
00:23:34,789 --> 00:23:37,291
I saw lawyers
coming out of Chair Kim's office earlier.

248
00:23:37,875 --> 00:23:40,169
It's pretty obvious why they were there.

249
00:23:40,253 --> 00:23:42,296
So how serious is the situation?

250
00:23:43,089 --> 00:23:46,050
Do you two really think Ms. Han
would do something like that?

251
00:23:46,134 --> 00:23:47,844
I don't want to believe it either,

252
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:50,429
but they say she was arrested
at the scene.

253
00:23:50,513 --> 00:23:52,056
What about the auction?

254
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:53,766
We've sent out
all the promotional materials.

255
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:55,643
Yeah. You think that's a problem?

256
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:58,563
One auctioneer fell to her death,
and the other just got arrested.

257
00:23:58,646 --> 00:24:00,064
No way.

258
00:24:00,898 --> 00:24:02,525
Could it be Yun-ji's curse?

259
00:24:03,609 --> 00:24:06,362
Oh, shit, that's spooky.
Brush it off your shoulder.

260
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:08,489
[Sang-mi] If you two keep chatting
instead of working,

261
00:24:08,573 --> 00:24:10,658
I might be the one putting a curse on you.

262
00:24:11,409 --> 00:24:13,035
But it's strange, isn't it?

263
00:24:13,119 --> 00:24:14,495
Ms. Han getting tangled up in this.

264
00:24:15,621 --> 00:24:16,914
Aren't you scared, Sang-mi?

265
00:24:16,998 --> 00:24:19,792
Not really. I'm more scared of you.

266
00:24:20,668 --> 00:24:22,795
Let's just keep preparing for the auction.

267
00:24:22,879 --> 00:24:25,381
The Stiller's out of the picture.
What auction is there?

268
00:24:25,464 --> 00:24:27,842
Ms. Han will return to work soon.

269
00:24:28,634 --> 00:24:31,179
Chair Kim is deeply concerned.

270
00:24:31,262 --> 00:24:33,431
The auction house's image has already
been damaged

271
00:24:33,514 --> 00:24:36,475
because of Ms. Kim's incident,
and now, a client has died.

272
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,569
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

273
00:24:47,695 --> 00:24:49,989
Well, to begin with,

274
00:24:50,072 --> 00:24:54,744
I would like you to resign and cooperate
so all of this can be settled quietly.

275
00:25:04,295 --> 00:25:05,880
Please tell Chair Kim

276
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:09,800
this won't hurt the company in any way.

277
00:25:10,384 --> 00:25:11,427
Ms. Han Seol-ah.

278
00:25:12,011 --> 00:25:13,888
Because I'm getting out of here.

279
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:21,062
Still nothing?

280
00:25:22,438 --> 00:25:23,522
[sighs]

281
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:27,151
Let me know as soon
as the results are in, okay?

282
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:33,574
The moment he revealed that he was Su-ho,

283
00:25:33,658 --> 00:25:35,284
his attitude totally changed.

284
00:25:35,785 --> 00:25:38,371
And if I'd come back as Lee Su-ho,

285
00:25:39,247 --> 00:25:40,915
would you have even noticed me?

286
00:25:40,998 --> 00:25:43,251
And when you found out
I had that Stiller piece,

287
00:25:43,334 --> 00:25:44,919
you came, wagging your tail!

288
00:25:45,002 --> 00:25:47,088
[breathing heavily]
We can be happy, Seol-ah.

289
00:25:47,171 --> 00:25:49,465
I'm Paek Jun-beom now, I can do anything.

290
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:51,008
I'll give you whatever you want, okay?

291
00:25:51,092 --> 00:25:52,468
- Huh? Huh?
- You've completely lost it!

292
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:53,970
[cackling]

293
00:25:57,223 --> 00:25:58,724
Get off me! Let go of me!

294
00:26:00,977 --> 00:26:02,645
I had to protect myself,

295
00:26:03,646 --> 00:26:05,856
so I grabbed whatever I could find
next to me.

296
00:26:07,692 --> 00:26:09,110
And then the power went out.

297
00:26:09,735 --> 00:26:10,945
[panting]

298
00:26:18,452 --> 00:26:19,453
[groans]

299
00:26:20,121 --> 00:26:21,497
Stay right here.

300
00:26:28,963 --> 00:26:31,299
[Seol-ah]
<i>I couldn't just stand there waiting.</i>

301
00:26:31,924 --> 00:26:33,926
So I went outside, and…

302
00:26:39,307 --> 00:26:40,308
Su-ho.

303
00:26:55,406 --> 00:26:57,199
- Su-ho…
- [gasping]

304
00:26:58,701 --> 00:27:00,202
[sobbing] Su-ho.

305
00:27:01,454 --> 00:27:02,955
Su-ho.

306
00:27:09,837 --> 00:27:11,839
[crying]

307
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:35,071
There was nothing more that I could do.

308
00:27:36,739 --> 00:27:38,449
[Eun-gyeom] Paek Jun-beom… I mean…

309
00:27:38,532 --> 00:27:41,994
Lee Su-ho had signs of pressure
around the wound.

310
00:27:42,078 --> 00:27:44,080
Someone tried to stop the bleeding?

311
00:27:46,082 --> 00:27:48,417
So, Ms. Han, based on your statement,

312
00:27:48,501 --> 00:27:50,920
there was someone else at the scene
where the murder took place,

313
00:27:51,003 --> 00:27:53,089
and that person is the killer?

314
00:27:54,423 --> 00:27:57,510
Don't answer anything you're not
sure about. Only say what you know.

315
00:28:00,096 --> 00:28:01,889
Well, think carefully now.

316
00:28:02,807 --> 00:28:06,852
Try to remember who you saw there

317
00:28:06,936 --> 00:28:09,980
and what you heard if you want to prove
you're not the killer.

318
00:28:11,315 --> 00:28:12,566
I have to prove it?

319
00:28:14,944 --> 00:28:16,737
Isn't that the police's job?

320
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:27,623
[sighs]

321
00:28:27,706 --> 00:28:28,707
[phone buzzes]

322
00:28:29,875 --> 00:28:30,876
Got the results?

323
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:33,087
[Eun-gyeom] <i>Sir,</i>
<i>the blood found on the tree</i>

324
00:28:33,170 --> 00:28:34,922
<i>matches the victim's blood.</i>

325
00:28:37,133 --> 00:28:39,385
Oh. Okay. Thanks.

326
00:28:42,304 --> 00:28:43,305
[line clicks]

327
00:28:47,101 --> 00:28:50,354
The blood recovered from the tree
matches the DNA of Paek Jun-beom…

328
00:28:50,438 --> 00:28:53,566
I mean, Lee Su-ho's DNA, actually.

329
00:28:54,442 --> 00:28:56,610
The two glove prints are also a match.

330
00:28:58,320 --> 00:28:59,321
[sighs]

331
00:29:01,532 --> 00:29:05,411
That means someone else was also
at the scene and fled.

332
00:29:05,494 --> 00:29:07,121
Yeah, it looks like it.

333
00:29:07,204 --> 00:29:09,582
And Han Seol-ah walks free again.

334
00:29:10,416 --> 00:29:12,585
We can't rule her out as a suspect yet.

335
00:29:12,668 --> 00:29:15,379
[sighs]
This is driving me nuts, seriously.

336
00:29:27,016 --> 00:29:28,184
Step aside.

337
00:29:28,267 --> 00:29:29,685
Where is she?

338
00:29:30,269 --> 00:29:31,562
She'll be out soon.

339
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:34,732
Don't let your guard down.

340
00:29:34,815 --> 00:29:37,234
She's still the prime suspect
of the investigation.

341
00:29:38,152 --> 00:29:39,820
She'll continue to be investigated.

342
00:29:39,904 --> 00:29:41,155
Well, shouldn't you track down

343
00:29:41,238 --> 00:29:42,990
the other person
who was at the scene first?

344
00:29:43,073 --> 00:29:44,825
That person is more likely the suspect,

345
00:29:45,618 --> 00:29:47,036
so can't you get a warrant?

346
00:29:48,537 --> 00:29:50,122
If I were you,

347
00:29:50,206 --> 00:29:52,374
I'd start by looking for the person
who first figured out

348
00:29:52,458 --> 00:29:54,293
that Paek Jun-beom was Lee Su-ho.

349
00:29:55,544 --> 00:29:57,213
And who's that?

350
00:29:57,296 --> 00:29:59,298
The person who did the allergy test.

351
00:30:00,674 --> 00:30:04,428
During the event, Paek Jun-beom
drank champagne and then collapsed.

352
00:30:09,308 --> 00:30:11,227
[Woo-seok] <i>He went</i>
<i>into anaphylactic shock.</i>

353
00:30:14,647 --> 00:30:16,774
It was clearly intentional.
Someone targeted him.

354
00:30:19,235 --> 00:30:20,778
Probably Han Seol-ah.

355
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,988
No, it wasn't her.

356
00:30:23,781 --> 00:30:27,201
It's true we tried to obtain a DNA sample
because we had our suspicions,

357
00:30:27,284 --> 00:30:30,496
but we never thought
he could be Lee Su-ho.

358
00:30:33,207 --> 00:30:35,626
Someone who knew about Lee Su-ho's allergy

359
00:30:36,377 --> 00:30:38,921
used it to test whether it
was really Paek Jun-beom or not.

360
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:49,014
[pensive music plays]

361
00:31:11,996 --> 00:31:13,247
[sighs]

362
00:31:31,056 --> 00:31:33,684
Ms. Han, you're not cleared
as a suspect just yet.

363
00:31:36,020 --> 00:31:38,647
The investigation is ongoing,
so don't go too far.

364
00:31:48,699 --> 00:31:50,909
Cha Woo-seok really cares.

365
00:31:53,787 --> 00:31:55,164
Don't drag him into this.

366
00:31:56,957 --> 00:31:58,542
If you cross the line,

367
00:31:59,168 --> 00:32:00,628
it'll hurt him too.

368
00:32:12,306 --> 00:32:13,307
[door opens]

369
00:32:38,916 --> 00:32:41,126
No matter how much
you want me out of this,

370
00:32:42,461 --> 00:32:44,213
don't ever lie
at the police station again.

371
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:48,384
You have to put yourself first,
no matter what.

372
00:32:48,467 --> 00:32:50,344
You saw it too, Woo-seok.

373
00:32:50,427 --> 00:32:53,889
Anyone would say I was caught red-handed,
so why did you believe me?

374
00:32:56,517 --> 00:32:59,603
'Cause I was tearing through the scene
all night like a madman.

375
00:33:00,229 --> 00:33:03,315
I was afraid I might actually find
evidence that you were guilty.

376
00:33:03,982 --> 00:33:06,819
[sighs] What would I do if I'd found it?

377
00:33:07,903 --> 00:33:09,196
It drove me crazy.

378
00:33:12,908 --> 00:33:14,660
I was afraid that I might get rid of it.

379
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:19,081
Even if you say you killed someone,

380
00:33:20,833 --> 00:33:22,042
I'll stay by your side.

381
00:33:24,962 --> 00:33:26,422
This is going to ruin you.

382
00:33:27,381 --> 00:33:28,382
No.

383
00:33:30,092 --> 00:33:31,677
It already has.

384
00:33:36,390 --> 00:33:37,558
Wait.

385
00:33:39,727 --> 00:33:40,894
Let's go to my place.

386
00:33:40,978 --> 00:33:43,814
Your place isn't safe, Seol-ah,
it was under surveillance.

387
00:33:44,398 --> 00:33:47,901
- Paek Jun-beom is already dead.
- But the killer is still alive.

388
00:33:54,700 --> 00:33:56,201
[sighs]

389
00:33:59,955 --> 00:34:02,082
Seol-ah. Seol-ah.

390
00:34:02,666 --> 00:34:03,667
Seol-ah!

391
00:35:27,501 --> 00:35:30,379
[sobbing] Su-ho.

392
00:35:37,803 --> 00:35:39,346
[whimpering]

393
00:35:58,574 --> 00:36:00,909
MEDICINE, HERBAL DRINK

394
00:36:19,511 --> 00:36:20,679
[door opens]

395
00:36:27,728 --> 00:36:28,937
Are you feeling better?

396
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:33,483
I should get going.

397
00:36:34,943 --> 00:36:35,944
No.

398
00:36:38,655 --> 00:36:39,865
You need to eat first.

399
00:36:41,158 --> 00:36:42,701
If you don't, you're not…

400
00:36:42,784 --> 00:36:43,785
I mean…

401
00:36:44,953 --> 00:36:45,954
I won't let you.

402
00:37:04,306 --> 00:37:06,683
For someone who insisted
you eat before leaving,

403
00:37:06,767 --> 00:37:08,518
the spread's a little underwhelming.

404
00:37:10,771 --> 00:37:14,733
Soup and rolled omelet
are the only things I know how to make.

405
00:37:17,277 --> 00:37:18,987
Oh, but the kimchi's really good.

406
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:22,282
Yeah. It was a gift.

407
00:37:24,409 --> 00:37:25,410
[chuckles]

408
00:37:27,579 --> 00:37:29,081
I'm not sure how it'll taste,

409
00:37:30,624 --> 00:37:32,209
but at least try a spoonful.

410
00:37:33,418 --> 00:37:34,920
They say food's the best medicine.

411
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:36,755
Hmm?

412
00:37:37,673 --> 00:37:40,008
Then why don't you eat with me, Woo-seok?

413
00:38:36,398 --> 00:38:37,566
[Suk-ji] At least eat this.

414
00:38:37,649 --> 00:38:39,609
Are you gonna stop eating
because of Seol-ah?

415
00:38:41,028 --> 00:38:42,988
[sighs] I'm so relieved she's finally out.

416
00:38:43,071 --> 00:38:45,157
Our Seol-ah really has the worst luck.

417
00:38:45,240 --> 00:38:47,617
Why are all the men around her like that?

418
00:38:48,118 --> 00:38:50,662
And how do they have
the same allergy? How bizarre?

419
00:38:51,913 --> 00:38:52,914
Allergy?

420
00:38:54,041 --> 00:38:56,251
Yeah. Remember Su-ho?

421
00:38:56,334 --> 00:38:57,377
He died in Syria?

422
00:38:59,296 --> 00:39:00,714
Seol-ah's first boyfriend?

423
00:39:02,215 --> 00:39:04,593
Remember Seol-ah's birthday,
we were having Thai food

424
00:39:04,676 --> 00:39:06,303
when Su-ho suddenly couldn't breathe.

425
00:39:06,386 --> 00:39:08,597
Maybe there were peanuts in the salad.

426
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:10,807
Seol-ah had to give him a shot then.

427
00:39:11,767 --> 00:39:12,768
Was that it?

428
00:39:15,020 --> 00:39:17,189
It was so long ago, I can't remember.

429
00:39:27,365 --> 00:39:28,533
Where are you going?

430
00:39:32,329 --> 00:39:33,497
Just stay here for a while.

431
00:39:34,081 --> 00:39:36,166
If it's uncomfortable,
I can go somewhere else.

432
00:39:36,249 --> 00:39:41,213
Our mutual agreement
to catch Paek Jun-beom is over.

433
00:39:42,255 --> 00:39:43,590
He's gone now.

434
00:39:43,673 --> 00:39:45,300
Paek Jun-beom is dead.

435
00:39:46,176 --> 00:39:47,427
We have to catch the killer.

436
00:39:48,345 --> 00:39:49,346
I…

437
00:39:50,514 --> 00:39:52,641
I lost Su-ho a long time ago.

438
00:39:53,225 --> 00:39:57,020
It was really shocking
that he came back and was still alive,

439
00:39:58,438 --> 00:40:00,357
and he died again because of me.

440
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:02,692
I told you already, it's not your fault.

441
00:40:04,903 --> 00:40:06,905
[slow ballad plays]

442
00:40:09,324 --> 00:40:11,368
I-I just don't think it's my place

443
00:40:12,119 --> 00:40:14,079
to grab on to your hand

444
00:40:15,914 --> 00:40:17,874
and lean on you for comfort.

445
00:40:21,878 --> 00:40:24,047
Don't do this. Please.

446
00:40:25,465 --> 00:40:27,342
Thank you so much.

447
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:30,387
I appreciate you

448
00:40:31,304 --> 00:40:32,472
for helping me

449
00:40:34,307 --> 00:40:35,433
and trusting me.

450
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:41,106
I'll never forget it.

451
00:40:50,699 --> 00:40:51,700
[sighs]

452
00:40:59,416 --> 00:41:00,417
Seol-ah.

453
00:41:01,126 --> 00:41:02,836
Please think it over, okay.

454
00:41:02,919 --> 00:41:04,546
You can't keep doing this.

455
00:41:04,629 --> 00:41:06,840
The killer is still alive.
This is dangerous!

456
00:41:06,923 --> 00:41:09,009
The killer is not after me,

457
00:41:09,092 --> 00:41:12,179
but after the man who's by my side.

458
00:41:27,569 --> 00:41:29,863
[song continues]

459
00:42:03,521 --> 00:42:05,607
[Woo-seok] <i>Did you really</i>
<i>just lose everything</i>

460
00:42:06,441 --> 00:42:08,652
<i>and have nothing to do with their deaths?</i>

461
00:42:08,735 --> 00:42:10,570
[Seol-ah] <i>The next man</i>
<i>who will fall in love…</i>

462
00:42:11,821 --> 00:42:12,864
<i>with Han Seol-ah…</i>

463
00:42:18,328 --> 00:42:21,873
[Woo-seok] <i>Usually, it's the adults</i>
<i>who create tragedies.</i>

464
00:42:23,792 --> 00:42:24,876
Will these do?

465
00:42:26,836 --> 00:42:28,672
I've never done this before.

466
00:42:33,426 --> 00:42:35,220
<i>Are you afraid that I'll get hurt?</i>

467
00:42:35,804 --> 00:42:37,097
You stayed strong

468
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:40,141
and you made it this far.

469
00:42:40,725 --> 00:42:42,352
You are not the villain here.

470
00:42:44,145 --> 00:42:45,397
You're a survivor.

471
00:43:08,545 --> 00:43:09,587
[Seol-ah] <i>Then don't</i>

472
00:43:10,922 --> 00:43:12,132
<i>get hurt. again.</i>

473
00:43:39,284 --> 00:43:40,285
[phone buzzes]

474
00:43:45,915 --> 00:43:48,251
[Dr. Shin] <i>Woo-seok,</i>
<i>I got Ju Hyun-su's address.</i>

475
00:43:57,427 --> 00:43:58,428
[door opens]

476
00:43:59,429 --> 00:44:00,597
[door closes]

477
00:44:11,524 --> 00:44:12,525
Ms. Han.

478
00:44:14,277 --> 00:44:15,820
[stammers] You're back.

479
00:44:16,780 --> 00:44:17,781
Where's Sang-mi?

480
00:44:18,365 --> 00:44:19,824
Mr. Song asked for her.

481
00:44:20,992 --> 00:44:23,370
We'll start our meeting in ten minutes.

482
00:44:24,037 --> 00:44:26,456
- Ow. Hey. What is it? Jeez.
- Get over here.

483
00:44:26,539 --> 00:44:28,750
- Ow, it snagged.
- What's going on, huh?

484
00:44:28,833 --> 00:44:30,794
I thought Ms. Han killed someone
and was getting fired.

485
00:44:30,877 --> 00:44:34,589
Well, I guess she didn't kill him,
she walked out and even came to work.

486
00:44:34,672 --> 00:44:37,884
Oh, come on.
She got dragged into an ugly scandal.

487
00:44:37,967 --> 00:44:40,387
And why would she follow a client
to his villa at night?

488
00:44:40,470 --> 00:44:43,431
Maybe they were dating or something. Why?

489
00:44:45,100 --> 00:44:48,478
Tae-seok, do you not understand
how serious this situation is?

490
00:44:49,229 --> 00:44:50,647
Yes, but either way,

491
00:44:51,272 --> 00:44:53,274
shouldn't we be backing
Ms. Han in this case?

492
00:44:53,358 --> 00:44:56,486
Are you that clueless,
or do you just have no ambition?

493
00:44:57,028 --> 00:44:58,655
I don't know about that.

494
00:44:58,738 --> 00:45:01,241
But I think I'm more loyal than you are.

495
00:45:02,117 --> 00:45:03,326
[scoffs]

496
00:45:32,647 --> 00:45:34,023
Oh.

497
00:45:34,107 --> 00:45:35,984
Oh, you poor thing.

498
00:45:36,067 --> 00:45:38,027
You've been through so much.

499
00:45:39,279 --> 00:45:42,657
Thank goodness. Seriously.
I'm so relieved.

500
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:44,826
I'm sorry for causing you concern.

501
00:45:45,827 --> 00:45:48,288
Do you have any idea how much I prayed?

502
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:52,000
Thanks to the attorney you sent,
we were able to resolve everything.

503
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:53,418
Thank you again.

504
00:45:53,501 --> 00:45:56,463
At times like this,
you shouldn't let yourself waiver.

505
00:45:56,546 --> 00:45:57,630
You need to be stronger.

506
00:45:58,214 --> 00:46:00,383
I will select the main piece
for the next auction

507
00:46:00,467 --> 00:46:02,886
and ensure everything
proceeds without a hitch.

508
00:46:02,969 --> 00:46:05,972
Just wrap it up
beautifully with your hands.

509
00:46:07,098 --> 00:46:10,185
That would be the greatest gift
you could give me.

510
00:46:19,277 --> 00:46:21,446
If she's done practicing, bring her in.

511
00:46:25,200 --> 00:46:26,201
[sighs]

512
00:46:27,202 --> 00:46:31,956
I wonder what would've happened
15 years ago if the former chairman

513
00:46:32,040 --> 00:46:34,459
hadn't fired me after the forgery scandal.

514
00:46:35,084 --> 00:46:37,795
When he refused to believe me,
I started a revolt,

515
00:46:37,879 --> 00:46:39,672
and with my backers' help,

516
00:46:39,756 --> 00:46:44,260
I was able to take over
the entire auction house.

517
00:46:46,137 --> 00:46:48,306
You turned a crisis into an opportunity.

518
00:46:48,389 --> 00:46:50,517
Life's full of turns.

519
00:46:50,600 --> 00:46:52,227
That's just how the world works.

520
00:46:52,310 --> 00:46:55,772
Something that seems bad at the time
can turn out

521
00:46:55,855 --> 00:46:58,066
- to be a blessing in disguise…
- [door opens]

522
00:46:58,149 --> 00:47:00,568
- …when you look back on it.
- [footsteps approaching]

523
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:08,826
We ran a mock auction, and she did great.

524
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:11,955
I'll put her through intensive training
and she'll be ready for the stage.

525
00:47:12,038 --> 00:47:13,998
Keep the handover smooth.

526
00:47:14,082 --> 00:47:16,501
But Ms. Han is back, isn't she?

527
00:47:16,584 --> 00:47:19,170
I heard we might need someone
to step in for the upcoming auction

528
00:47:19,254 --> 00:47:21,923
while you were under investigation.
That's why I've been practicing.

529
00:47:22,006 --> 00:47:25,093
Just because we're in the arts

530
00:47:25,176 --> 00:47:28,972
doesn't mean we can afford to let
our emotions carry us away.

531
00:47:29,055 --> 00:47:32,976
When the air in the room changes,
paintings reveal themselves in a new way.

532
00:47:33,059 --> 00:47:34,227
Ms. Han.

533
00:47:34,936 --> 00:47:36,229
You should take a break.

534
00:47:39,232 --> 00:47:40,650
So you're going to…

535
00:47:42,527 --> 00:47:44,320
kick me out after everything?

536
00:47:44,904 --> 00:47:49,033
Go work at the Busan office
for a while, all right? Hmm?

537
00:47:52,829 --> 00:47:56,541
Then this could turn out to be
another opportunity for me…

538
00:47:58,543 --> 00:48:00,545
just like you back in the day, ma'am.

539
00:48:07,969 --> 00:48:09,095
[Sang-mi] Ms. Han!

540
00:48:13,057 --> 00:48:15,351
It wasn't my intention.
Please don't get the wrong impression.

541
00:48:16,227 --> 00:48:19,105
It's harder to keep a position
than to attain one on your own,

542
00:48:19,939 --> 00:48:22,275
especially when
you didn't earn it yourself.

543
00:48:22,859 --> 00:48:24,360
I'm well aware of that.

544
00:48:24,444 --> 00:48:26,779
But I know you'll do well, Sang-mi.

545
00:48:28,072 --> 00:48:29,407
You've learned so much.

546
00:48:30,033 --> 00:48:31,993
It's about time you took up the stage.

547
00:48:33,202 --> 00:48:34,370
Ms. Han.

548
00:48:34,454 --> 00:48:36,956
Just stand by me one last time.

549
00:48:37,540 --> 00:48:38,583
Please.

550
00:48:43,838 --> 00:48:45,131
[Eun-gyeom] This is it.

551
00:48:46,466 --> 00:48:48,134
His house.

552
00:48:48,217 --> 00:48:49,218
His car.

553
00:48:50,428 --> 00:48:51,429
His face.

554
00:48:52,263 --> 00:48:53,723
Is that him?

555
00:49:00,647 --> 00:49:02,482
This bastard, I knew it was him.

556
00:49:02,565 --> 00:49:04,067
The moment I saw that older model car,

557
00:49:04,150 --> 00:49:06,944
bam, I had a gut feeling
I should look into him.

558
00:49:07,528 --> 00:49:09,864
And sure enough,
the plate came back canceled.

559
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:12,367
Guess I'm half detective now…

560
00:49:16,454 --> 00:49:18,164
[lawyer] <i>Ms. Cha,</i>
<i>was in the passenger seat,</i>

561
00:49:18,247 --> 00:49:19,832
<i>was not wearing a seat belt,</i>

562
00:49:19,916 --> 00:49:22,710
<i>and a sleep inducing agent</i>
<i>was detected in her bloodstream.</i>

563
00:49:23,378 --> 00:49:25,338
<i>At the recommendation of defendant</i>
<i>Ju Hyun-su,</i>

564
00:49:25,421 --> 00:49:28,883
<i>she had taken out a two hundred and ten</i>
<i>thousand dollar life insurance policy.</i>

565
00:49:30,093 --> 00:49:32,178
Die, you son of a bitch!

566
00:49:32,261 --> 00:49:33,471
[shouts]

567
00:49:52,949 --> 00:49:55,326
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

568
00:49:56,953 --> 00:50:00,289
ROYAL VILLAT

569
00:50:01,624 --> 00:50:02,750
[knocks on door]

570
00:50:06,838 --> 00:50:09,006
Next week's auction
is really your last one?

571
00:50:09,882 --> 00:50:10,883
Uh.

572
00:50:11,467 --> 00:50:15,096
The attorney came to the police station
with a resignation letter.

573
00:50:15,179 --> 00:50:16,723
But you just got out.

574
00:50:16,806 --> 00:50:17,890
Weren't the charges dropped?

575
00:50:19,684 --> 00:50:21,394
Try talking to the company again.

576
00:50:21,477 --> 00:50:22,854
If you tell them
that you've been cleared--

577
00:50:22,937 --> 00:50:25,690
It'll be hard to get Chair Kim
to backtrack on her decision.

578
00:50:25,773 --> 00:50:27,483
After everything you've been through
to get this far?

579
00:50:27,567 --> 00:50:30,987
It's okay. Now I can finally do
what I have to do.

580
00:50:31,779 --> 00:50:34,073
[sighs] Uh. Do you have another
auction house in mind?

581
00:50:34,157 --> 00:50:35,867
It's not that.

582
00:50:36,492 --> 00:50:38,995
I've got something personal
I have to deal with.

583
00:50:39,078 --> 00:50:40,288
I'll see you later.

584
00:50:51,466 --> 00:50:53,384
HYUN-SU'S FRUIT

585
00:50:58,848 --> 00:51:01,851
WE'VE CLOSED DOWN FOR PERSONAL REASONS
THANK YOU FOR YOUR SUPPORT

586
00:51:10,610 --> 00:51:11,986
[gasps]

587
00:51:12,069 --> 00:51:13,196
You scared me.

588
00:51:13,696 --> 00:51:14,781
Oh, sorry.

589
00:51:15,281 --> 00:51:17,158
I was worried, so I followed you.

590
00:51:18,993 --> 00:51:21,078
This place. Why are you here?

591
00:51:23,372 --> 00:51:25,333
Can't you just tell me right now?

592
00:51:26,250 --> 00:51:30,004
I'm digging into Chair Kim's properties
under pseudonyms.

593
00:51:30,087 --> 00:51:32,924
I have a feeling Taemyung's paintings
might be in there.

594
00:51:33,591 --> 00:51:35,760
Didn't they all burn up
in the car accident?

595
00:51:35,843 --> 00:51:37,220
Those were all fakes.

596
00:51:37,845 --> 00:51:40,306
I think the real ones
were hidden somewhere else.

597
00:51:41,474 --> 00:51:42,934
So you think they're in this house?

598
00:51:43,017 --> 00:51:44,977
It doesn't look like anyone lives here.

599
00:51:47,063 --> 00:51:48,147
Follow me.

600
00:51:56,823 --> 00:51:58,491
All the meters are shut off.

601
00:51:59,283 --> 00:52:02,328
It's a redevelopment zone,
so they probably moved everyone out.

602
00:52:03,329 --> 00:52:06,374
Starting tomorrow, focus on getting ready
for the auction.

603
00:52:06,457 --> 00:52:08,000
I'll check out the properties for you.

604
00:52:08,084 --> 00:52:09,710
You'll suffer the consequences as well.

605
00:52:09,794 --> 00:52:11,254
That's fine.

606
00:52:11,337 --> 00:52:14,799
I really don't wanna be there
without you anyway.

607
00:52:15,383 --> 00:52:16,676
You have to stop.

608
00:52:17,760 --> 00:52:20,888
Focus on yourself
instead of focusing on me.

609
00:52:20,972 --> 00:52:21,973
Stop it.

610
00:52:23,015 --> 00:52:24,308
Stop doing that.

611
00:52:34,026 --> 00:52:35,027
[door opens]

612
00:52:37,196 --> 00:52:38,197
[door closes]

613
00:52:38,906 --> 00:52:39,907
[device beeps]

614
00:53:11,898 --> 00:53:14,150
HAN SEOL-AH

615
00:53:30,458 --> 00:53:32,710
HAN SEOL-AH

616
00:54:10,665 --> 00:54:12,416
GANGHA POLICE STATION

617
00:54:12,500 --> 00:54:13,584
CHEONGUN CELL TOWER 3 CONNECTION LOG

618
00:54:13,668 --> 00:54:15,503
CELL TOWER DEVICE ACCESS LOG

619
00:54:16,087 --> 00:54:17,505
[Eun-gyeom]
I checked the cell tower records,

620
00:54:17,588 --> 00:54:20,841
Paek Jun-beom wasn't anywhere near
Yoon Seung-jae when he died.

621
00:54:20,925 --> 00:54:24,595
And he left the Royal Auction building
before Kim Yun-ji fell.

622
00:54:24,679 --> 00:54:27,848
If Paek Jun-beom wasn't the one
who killed the men around Han Seol-ah…

623
00:54:28,766 --> 00:54:31,894
That makes him the latest victim then.

624
00:54:35,272 --> 00:54:37,358
Start by tracking
who prepared the champagne

625
00:54:37,441 --> 00:54:39,568
that Paek Jun-beom drank,
and where it came from.

626
00:54:40,653 --> 00:54:42,488
That's the only clue we have.

627
00:54:43,114 --> 00:54:46,951
The champagne was probably brought in
by Hwang Suk-ji.

628
00:54:48,953 --> 00:54:51,664
And then the staff served it.

629
00:54:55,167 --> 00:54:57,753
NAME: DO EUN-HYE

630
00:55:03,300 --> 00:55:05,344
INTERROGATION ROOM

631
00:55:18,232 --> 00:55:19,233
What about it?

632
00:55:19,316 --> 00:55:21,902
Could you please explain
exactly what happened that day?

633
00:55:23,904 --> 00:55:25,573
I went about my work as usual.

634
00:55:25,656 --> 00:55:27,033
I don't really have anything to explain.

635
00:55:27,700 --> 00:55:29,744
Where did the champagne
you served come from?

636
00:55:31,328 --> 00:55:32,913
Did you open it, Ms. Do?

637
00:55:39,253 --> 00:55:41,130
We obviously tested the champagne

638
00:55:41,213 --> 00:55:44,842
and we actually found that peanut
powder had been added to it.

639
00:55:45,634 --> 00:55:48,429
Can you please explain what happened now?

640
00:55:52,975 --> 00:55:54,894
Hey. Ms. Do Eun-hye.

641
00:55:56,270 --> 00:55:57,521
I don't remember.

642
00:56:00,524 --> 00:56:03,486
Then do you remember
following the victim that day?

643
00:56:05,071 --> 00:56:06,072
[button clicks]

644
00:56:25,424 --> 00:56:28,594
[Gong] Is this also part of your job?

645
00:56:30,387 --> 00:56:33,724
Ms. Do, we're asking you to tell us
what you did, all right.

646
00:56:59,291 --> 00:57:01,293
[dynamic music plays]

647
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:49,258
RECIPIENT: HAN SEO-YUL

648
00:57:50,467 --> 00:57:52,219
[Woo-seok] <i>It's similar</i>
<i>to my sister's accident.</i>

649
00:57:52,803 --> 00:57:54,638
The driver is only 23.

650
00:57:54,722 --> 00:57:57,933
When moving high-value paintings
like these, you never do it alone.

651
00:57:58,642 --> 00:58:01,187
So if the paintings were insured
and someone deliberately burned them,

652
00:58:01,270 --> 00:58:03,522
they could collect the full 1.05 million?

653
00:58:03,606 --> 00:58:05,482
Criminals stick to familiar tactics

654
00:58:06,192 --> 00:58:07,985
and repeat methods that worked before.

655
00:58:11,155 --> 00:58:13,157
[dynamic music continues]

656
00:59:09,713 --> 00:59:10,881
[elevator bell dings]

657
01:00:16,780 --> 01:00:18,032
{\an8}The man you just saw…

658
01:00:19,658 --> 01:00:22,453
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>Ju Hyun-su,</i>
<i>Chair Kim's henchman.</i>

659
01:00:22,536 --> 01:00:24,580
{\an8}Do you want me
to take a guess why you're here?

660
01:00:24,663 --> 01:00:26,415
{\an8}Congrats, Ms. Han!

661
01:00:26,498 --> 01:00:28,792
{\an8}<i>I heard that the Stiller piece</i>
<i>is yours now.</i>

662
01:00:28,876 --> 01:00:30,961
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>There was evidence</i>
<i>the paintings were moved here.</i>

663
01:00:31,045 --> 01:00:33,505
{\an8}There is one
that the employees can't access.

664
01:00:33,589 --> 01:00:36,884
{\an8}We have only one week to get in.

665
01:00:37,634 --> 01:00:39,136
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>Are you sure you'll be okay?</i>

666
01:00:39,219 --> 01:00:40,512
{\an8}<i>I'm offering you an opportunity.</i>

667
01:00:40,596 --> 01:00:41,847
{\an8}[Eun-gyeom]
<i>The auctioneer should get out fast.</i>

668
01:00:41,930 --> 01:00:43,265
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>Seol-ah?</i>

669
01:00:43,349 --> 01:00:46,018
{\an8}<i>And you're still saying</i>
<i>this is your last one?</i>

